synopsis: After destroying the Bavarian Illuminati, the Symphogear wielders head to the poles, to recover a powerful precursor artifact. But the artifact isn't as dead as it appears...
After the disasterous battle at the pole, the team regroups in Tokyo. Tsubasa prepares for her comeback concert, but the enemy has plans for it...
Tsubasa is devastated after the deaths at the concert. Noble Red's struggles to survive are revealed.
The Symphogear Weilders track down and are on the verge of defeating Noble Red, when the Japanese government intervenes to stop them.
The government has temporarily shut down SONG, and the Wielders are put on a short break. But the enemy uses this time to strike...
Miku is gone, and so is Elfnein. The enemy has taken them, and it's up to the Symphogear Wielders to get them back.
The Wielders find the Fool's Stone, and can now use their powerful Ignite modules against their alchemist foes. Cagliostro is the first to challenge them and their new power...

The group trains so that everyone can pair with any other team member and use their powerful Unison attacks. But Shirabe is having trouble pairing up with anybody but Kirika, because of her inability to trust others.

With what they've learned from the shrine, the Symphogear Wielders now know the full extent of the Illumanti's plan: they're going to use an ancient gate to summon the power of a god. Only one person can stop them: Hibiki, the "God-Killer".
The divine power chooses Hibiki as its vessel. To stop the worldwide disaster she could cause, the U.N. initiates a wide-scale attack on Japan.
